The paper deals with problems in geometry processing, computer vision, and graphics, which are typically covered by the sub-categories of computer graphics (cs.GR), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), computational geometry (cs.CG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and sound and music computing (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on the Laplacian spectrum and its applications in shape reconstruction, pose and style transfer, and dense deformable correspondence, which are all relevant to these sub-categories. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
